# Sprint 3.1 – Phase 4: Authentication API Implementation Plan

This implementation plan covers the delivery of the HTTP API routes exposing the user authentication services (`AuthService`, `JWTService`, `PasswordService`). The routes will be registered under `backend/app/routes/auth.py`.

---

## Architecture Notes

* **Thin Routes**: Routers will only validate JSON payloads (automatically via Pydantic schemas), invoke stateless services, catch custom service layer exceptions, and return serialized Pydantic responses.
* **Separation of Concerns**: Cryptography (bcrypt), token operations (jose), and database transaction management remain isolated inside the service layer.
* **API Documentation**: The endpoints will be fully decorated with descriptions, response classes, and explicit error status code schemas to ensure FastAPI's Swagger UI (`/docs`) accurately represents all possible outputs.

---

## Exception Mapping Strategy

We will map service-layer exceptions to FastAPI `HTTPException` responses as follows:

| Service-Layer Exception | HTTP Status Code | Response Detail / Message |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `UserAlreadyExistsError` | `409 Conflict` | `"A user with this email address already exists"` |
| `InvalidCredentialsError` | `401 Unauthorized` | `"Invalid email or password"` |
| `UserNotFoundError` | `404 Not Found` | `"User not found"` |
| `TokenExpiredError` | `401 Unauthorized` | `"Could not validate credentials"` (via `get_current_user`) |
| `TokenInvalidError` | `401 Unauthorized` | `"Could not validate credentials"` (via `get_current_user`) |
| `Exception` (unhandled database/infra error) | `500 Internal Server Error` | `"An internal server error occurred"` |

